values: Alright...i'm moving on...i'm done caring...if she changes her mind ever fine...whatever maybe i'll consider it but i'm not planning on it...i'm just tired of feeling...things...i'm done i'm going to put myself back into the isolation i usually hold myself to and deal with life that way...But i don't need this anymore...I'm done trying to keep things alive...thats how it always was...I was always putting the effort in...and getting little back...well fuck that...it's good i guess...i felt like i wasn't being appreciated anyways...and that feeling is just getting stronger...so welcome back John...i'm good...anyways...watching boondock saints right now...happy saint patty's day everyone...

you know what i just realised...when people picture hell they picture red...fire........but the hottest color is technically violet...well violet blue...red is actually cooler...hmmm....people are stupid...thats all...take a guess as to how i feel based on that statement...

stressful week...hmmm...and having a car doesn't make it easier then it was when i didn't have one...now everyone expects me to be everywhere when they want me to be...it's not that simple...i have things to do, work to take care of...homework...eh....so tired already...and it'll be worse once i get working on sound stuff... and then technical director as well..god...bad term to take all general ed classes...especially english and astronomy...to much work...grrr.anways..i'm bored and i'm taking a break from english work...and i'm poor cause i don't have a real job right now....if anyone has any ideas it would be nice for some help finding a job...i just need something that pays decent i...i don't know anything really...you guys know how hard i'd work...anyways...hmmm i'm in a wierd state right now....not sure where i'm going...kinda hesitant with whats in my life right now...but i'm happy..so i don't know....i guess i'm just a bit freaked out...so much happening, so much to worry about i don't know if i can handle it all....i mean i did before but that was when i was still at liberty, school was easy and i was already always at the PAC i could do things faster then, now i have to go from school to liberty and i have to manage everything else and it's a little bit harder than it used to be, but i don't know....a bit more rewarding this time around, gah, i bet i'm confusing whoever reads this...if anyone reads this....mer...lifes wierd everybody...okay whatever i gotta get back to work, this will be something to think about at a later date.

Lomon' is short for Lomond, it is probably spelled this way to allow

.
The song was apparantly written by a young soldier to his sweetheart. Two
of Bonnie Prince Charlies soldiers were captured in Carlisle after the
abortive rising of 1745. One wrote the song, the other was released and
took it back to Scotland to give to his colleagues sweetheart. The low
road refers to the soldiers impending death and the path of his spirit,
whilst the high road is either the sign of hope for which he sacrificed
his life, or the actual road back to Scotland over the high rugged hills.
Hence, his spirit would return via the low road and be back in Scotland
first.

Well...it's done, it's over...hmmm...you know what...i wish it wasn't...I had more fun last night then I have in I don't know how long...it's wierd. For 4 years i've been running away from mainstream stuff like dances...and parties...i never imagined i would have fun because i found those things to be utterly embarrassing and pointless...Why would someone have fun at a dance when the danceing isn't even that good and half the time neither is the music. I was wrong...it was so much fun and i regret not going to them before this...now i won't have the chance ever again...I danced...those that know me know that I DON'T DANCE...But I did...thanks Vicki...lol...if she hadn't gone with me I probably wouldn't have danced and I probably would have been extremely miserable...but she made it fun...It WAS a night to remember and I am very happy I did go...I saw a lot of people there and realised how many people I actually knew...theres a lot of them...it's crazy....hmmmm....With all this going through my head I am going to give some advice...To any of you that read this...any of you younger kids....Have fun...don't be like me...don't think that it's immature to goto dances that it will be boring and don't be scared of dancing...you'll miss out... I swear it's fun just find someone your comfortable with and dance...who cares if you can't ...nobody else can and while you might feel awkward at first you'll stop caring cause you'll realise nobody cares if you can dance...what matters is that you have fun...enjoy your youth and live for the day...Theres no day but today....
i feel like saying something...ironic...poetic...insightful and brilliant. Unfortunatly all i can come up with is this....matters of the heart should be doused with gasoline and lit on fire.

Tired
lingering on the edge,
a dream like state,
half awake,
or half asleep,
are they real
is it my imagination
those monsters
leave me scared
hunched over
cowering
kicking
hiding in a corner
screaming to get away
razor sharp,
fine cuts,
blood flowing 
my life drains away
i watch on
feeling every slice
every searing pain
the wounds heal instantly
only to be cut even deeper
the pool of blood 
flowing across the floor
my vision clouding
my senses numb
my body dying
as my heart beats 
for the very last time

Your #1 Match: INFJ

The Protector You live your life with integrity, originality, vision, and creativity. Independent and stubborn, you rarely stray from your vision - no matter what it is. You are an excellent listener, with almost infinite patience. You have complex, deep feelings, and you take great care to express them. You would make a great photographer, alternative medicine guru, or teacher.

Your #2 Match: INFP

The Idealist You are creative with a great imagination, living in your own inner world. Open minded and accepting, you strive for harmony in your important relationships. It takes a long time for people to get to know you. You are hesitant to let people get close. But once you care for someone, you do everything you can to help them grow and develop. You would make an excellent writer, psychologist, or artist.

Your #3 Match: INTJ

The Scientist You have a head for ideas - and you are good at improving systems. Logical and strategic, you prefer for everything in your life to be organized. You tend to be a bit skeptical. You're both critical of yourself and of others. Independent and stubborn, you tend to only befriend those who are a lot like you. You would make an excellent scientist, engineer, or programmer.

Hey everyone. I guess i am gonna post in here and make everything pretty simple and straight if anyone actually cares...I'm single i believe everyone knew that....I'm kinda/ kinda not looking for another relationship right now it all depends on the person....Anyways that's the one thing i'm not gonna write about cause i'm not ready to yet...Still sorting things out i guess. The show is over... I miss it, i miss having a reason for being there all day long, i miss talking to people certain persons in particular... I made some knew friends this show and strengthened one friendship which i'm very glad about and yeah i'll post more on that later maybe...This show was difficult...it was. There are only two things i can really think about one is well yeah again, i'm not ready to talk about it yet...The other is the ghost light ceremony...This time was so different from the other shows i've done. At every other ghost lighting i have stayed for a really long time....i tried to force myself to cry in the past...i never could and i felt so....so wrong that i couldn't...But this time i stayed for maybe 5 minutes until i left because i was crying....i was and it was so ....different. When i handed Dixon that script i just could barely stand....And when she hugged me and said thank you i almost burst into tears there.......It was ...i don't know....i just don't know it was such a different experience and it scared me....it scared me to think that i have one show left....only one...I'm afraid....a few of you know what i want to do with my life....for those who don't i want to work at Disneyland as a lighting technician....It's a wierd goal but when you think about it...they are the best....you have to be the best to work there....so thats where i want to end up working for disney....kinda strange i know but it's true....and that's why i'm afraid... I'm realising how hard it's gonna be to get there all the work it will be but....it's my dream....I'm glad i did this show....i am. I'm glad i got to work with all of you .... I'm just getting really freaked out at the prospect that i won't be at liberty for much longer... This is my last year as a student and i might be there for next year too i'm not sure. Life is strange ya know...one minute your a lowly freshmen and the next thing you know your up on stage in the dark praying for a little more time....Praying for a way to keep it all and not have to say goodbye to the friends i know i won't ever see again after June....For all you underclassmen don't start thinking about it yet...it'll only make you sad and you need to have fun still. you need to push those feelings away until your senior year so you don't feel the pain....it's funny you know...you think you aren't that attached to anyone or anyplace and then you realise your trapped and you like it...I want everyone to have fun this year....For some of us it isn't as fun anymore... some let it die....to some of you it may just be a hobby, others might think of it as a job....but to those few myself included....it's a calling.... What i'm trying to say is Theatre can make or break you...don't let it break you....love it and you'll be fine. Goodnight my friends.
